==English==
===Etymology===
[[Category:Latin derivations]]
From Latin [[mortalis]], from [[mortis]], [[mors]] ‘death’, from Indo-European ''*mor-'' ‘die’ (the source of [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[μόρος]]''' (moros) ‘doom, death, corpse’, Old English [[morþ]] ‘murder’, Welsh [[marw]] ‘died’, Lithuanian [[mirtis]] ‘mortal’).

===Adjective===
'''mortal'''

# Susceptible to death by aging or sickness

====Antonyms====
*[[immortal]]

====Derived terms====
*[[mortality]]
*[[mortal sin]]

